Body: Description: All client reporting expired endpoint cert- i am uninstalling all clients one by one-Need immediate call back 978-729-2546
Invitation updated. Attendees: No attendees listed
Invitation updated. Attendees: Eduard Nut, Philip Sullivan

What We've Learned Updated: During the meeting, I saw that the certificate we use for DPI did not refresh on the computers and the reason is still unknown.
As a fix, we uninstalled the agent using the zap tool since regular uninstall left some remnants and the new agent would error out, and then install it again after a reboot. This solved the issue with the certificate.
We also started a client upgrade process from the console so that all computers refresh the certificate when they get the latest available agent.
Next Steps Updated: waiting on the customer to get back to me regarding the agent upgrade process we started, and to see how we go about the server and agents upgrade to the latest one available.

What We've Learned Updated: to upgrade I strongly recommended having a snapshot done and since that was not possible during the call, the customer will get back to me and set up a new meeting to upgrade form 5600 to 5941.
before upgrading I will make sure to explain the client upgrade process.
need to start at 5650 offline and continue from there.
Next Steps Updated: waiting on the customer to get back to me today or tomorrow and set up a new meeting

What We've Learned Updated: upgraded to 5700 and ran an upgrade job for the agents since the customer does not use an MDM tool.
when that is done we need to upgrade a few more to still be in the range of 5 versions to use the upgrade process form the console.
recommend upgrading to 5910 and upgrading the agents again before moving on

What We've Learned Updated: The customer is still waiting for an upgrade job to finish and then based on our meeting and the guide I sent him, he will upgrade to 5900 and then upgrade the agents again.
